item.title: FreeSpirit Summer Camp - Kernow International Jamboree
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded:
The time is almost upon us for the highlight of the year - our Summer Camp. This year we travel to the Pencarrow Estate near Bodmin in Cornwall.

Please check these pages regularly to keep up with all the fun and exploits. Feel free to add a comment and join in.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: How's it all going? Did you have to put the tents up in the rain? Hope everything is okay.

item.title: Saturday...a long day
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: The day dawned and was nice and sunny...it even rained bacon butties! The van was packed...tents, stoves...even the kitchen sink....and then the youngsters arrived. The usual team pose was taken and we hit the road expecting a 3-4 hour drive...7 hours later finally found us on the Pencarrow estate in Cornwall. The M5 had been carnage from just south of Bristol! The Jamboree site looks pretty good...although not too many flags on display ..the camp won't know what hit them in the morning when our army of flags arrives! Much more tomorrow.

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Another day spent in the m5 carpark. Lovely

item.title: Bodmin, Padstow...and a few flags
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Today was a rest day. But a full English breakfast was still in order...bacon, black pudding,  eggy bread, beans, mushrooms.  We decided to head over to Bodmin to check out the stunning entertainment...and found it shut! So we went to Padstow...sun, scenery,  a brass band...and a Cornish Pasty! Following tea, we broke out the flags (25 of them) got into uniform and headed over for the opening ceremony. ..and ruled the school.  We had more flags than the whole camp!!! Two Scouts opened the Jamboree and a local band, Ricky Business, did a fantastic set and got us all dancing. Check out Cassie's new hair!!

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Nice to see the photos but they are a bit small and you cant enlaarge them. Any chance of posting slightly bigger ones

item.title: Energise and Bushcraft
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: The day dawned,  good coffee was drunk....and then about 6" of rain fell in half an hour!! ....but this was then followed by glorious sunshine. The morning found us all in Energise - mad activities to start the day...circus skills and balloon modeling. This was followed by a hike into the nearby woods for Bushcraft skills and and a sleep out in shelters. Fire starting, knife and axe craft, shelter building and backwoods cooking...more info when they return tomorrow.

item.title: A flock of sheep and a ransom!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: In our "essential" kit lurked a flock of sheep with their trusty sheep dog (Dilwyn), superbly manufactured by Osama's Dad Bin Brewing. Late last night our intrepid sheep slipped their faithful dog a mickey fin sending him off to the land of nod whereupon they scattered. Morning light found our flock attached to flag poles, gateways and tents throughout the Jamboree.....then came tbe ransom note! Apparently one of our sheep (Rhod) had been sheep-napped. A 12 oclock deadline had been issued and we had to bring cake!! We laid our plans....a Swiss roll was laced with chilli, 100 water bombs were filled, the Super Soakers were fueled and we placed our ambush. Cassie waited by the main flagpole and the exchange was done...as our sheep-knapper made to leave, all hell exploded....episode 2 coming soon!

item.title: Angry Chuffs and a talent show
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Today started with some light rain and the end of the Bushcraft activity. This was followed by an afternoon on the Creative base where a flock of "Angry Chuffs" (a Cornish bird) were created and added to our fleet of mascots - Dodgy Bob our pigeon;  Bjion our snake; our singing moose and lobster and our sheep. Following tea we headed for the main stage and the nights talent show. Jim opened will a great solo on guitar and was followed by Lauren and Amy (also on guitar)...2 great songs that went down very well.  We wait for the verdict from the judges! The night ended with a great beach party, neon mad Welsh disco...a good  day.

item.title: Adventure time!
item.dc:creator: Becky
item.content:encoded: Today found us in Adventure Zone...caving, zip wire, archery, assault course, low ropes, speed orienteering,  gocarting, shooting and climbing. We set the site record for the orienteering,  and did very well in the assault course and Shooting...with a new unit snipper champion - Callum!

item.title: Sheep-knapping...an update
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Following our sweet revenge on our sheep-knapper, the site media team wanted a comment and a photo...and guess what? Today we made the cover of the Jamboree newsletter! We also decided to "decorate" our sheep-knapping neighbours tent in retaliation! !

item.title: Cornish Ceilidh
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Following an excellent display from an American Scout Taikwando team, Wednesday night found us in front of the main stage with a live band and a ceilidh. 800 people doing a line dance....stunning. A stunning theme was also emerging. Our older members were being seriously shown up by our newer members in the "new female friend" department...watch this space!

item.title: GDVAnd Hot Air
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Thursday morning found us in the Global Development Village facing a number of challenging issues...global disaster and dealing with it with a disability, Shelter Box..emergency kit for disaster relief,  inspirational messages, on line safety and emergency grab bags....a truly thought provoking time. After lunch, Air zone found us doing human table football,  bouncy assault course,  jousting,  sumo suits,...and many more...a fun afternoon.

item.title: Investitures, Promises...and Ruling the School (again!)
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Early evening found us in front of the main camp flagpole with the whole jamboree assembling as we invested Sam, Jack, Josh and Dave. Smart uniforms were the order of the day...so Buff and Rhys dressed in the unit dragon suits and Lukas and Jim wore Welsh Flag dresses. Naturally the investiture proceeded in true FreeSpirit fashion to the applause of the whole camp. Many other groups then wanted to have their photos taken with the wonderful Welsh!

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: James this crossdressing thing is going a bit too far you seem to be enjoying it a bit toooo much But then again you do have the legs for it!!!! Minsky's next? Glad you are all enjoying yourselves!

item.title: an apology
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Sorry for the lack of photos and blog entries. ..but there is little or no Internet on site! This blog is being run from Buff's phone and 3G signal!

item.title: Team Lady Lube Strikes Again!!!
item.dc:creator: Becky
item.content:encoded: While waiting for the male leaders to deliberate which souvenirs they were going to relocate, Team Lady Lube struck at midnight. Their first outing was at Essex Jamboree last year and they didn't disappoint this summer, nabbing the one banner the male leaders really wanted...

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: ahem I think you'll find team lube hit 1st and got the p*****l :-) have fun!!

item.title: Birthdays, Radio Cornwall and Coasteering
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Today was a special day. Not only were we off to the coast for some sea kayaking,  canoeing,  surfing and coasteering....it was also Josh and Abi's birthdays. Following breakfast we put up birthday banners and presented our birthday due with cards and a big birthday badge which they had to wear all day. This was followed by Jamal's interview with Radio Cornwall representing all the Explorers on the Jamboree. ..another FreeSpirit first. Watersports were fantastic. ..the sun was shining and the sea was bouncing nicely. We did a mixture of all three sports, with the addition of some rock jumping and some mad swimming and capsizing. Then back home to site for a superb chilli followed by the closing ceremony.

item.title: Closing Ceremony
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: We pulled on our dragon suits and onsies for the last time and paraded down to the main stage for the closing ceremony. Following the inevitable thank you's, we were entertained by "Counterfeit Kylie" who did a number of the real artists songs. This was followed by the final of the tallent show, in which our very own Jim was competing. A final set by lookie likey Lady Ga Ga completed the evening. It was now time to party back at our tent and say goodbye to new friends. ...which seemed to involve a lot of hand holding for some of us!

item.title: Final moments...Bear Gryls, David Walliams and some dubloons
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded:
This morning saw us all packing like mad before an excellent breakfast of pancakes. The sun was still shining when the unit headed off to finish our last programme zone...Eco. And was still shining when a helicopter dropped in and off loaded Chief Scout Bear Gryls and comedian David Walliams. They wandered throughout the camp leaving happy and amazed young people in their wake.

Our kit was packed when a party of pirates was spotted approaching...it was our sheep rustling fiends from Red Bandits ESU. They presented us with an ancient pirate scroll and a small treasure chest filled with dubloons and a message -"FreeSpirit ESU, Thanks for some top rated plundering at Kernow Jamboree, your friends The Midnight Fleet and Red Bandits ESU". Goodbyes were said and we hit the road home.

item.title: Blog Update and home time
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: This blog and our photo gallery will be seriously updated tomorrow with many more photos and stories...be sure to check back. We are hoping to get away around 12-1pm arriving back at the hut at 6ish...but will update you all from the road.

item.title: A new Mess Tent Mobile!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Earlier in the week, our new good neighbours and fiends from Aldershot made the mistake in going off site on an activity day...we then decided that their campsite needed a little facelift...well, today they returned the compliment in style! A cross of St George was added to our main flagpole, and a cool "mobile", using most of our kitchen items, was added to the interior of our mess tent. An idea that we have now added to our repertoire for another time!

item.title: A missing banner...
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: We awoke this morning to find that our new FreeSpirit banner, complete with the Kernow logo, had gone missing. Following our sheep rustling incidents and subsequent ransom notes, we eagerly awaited the next installment...but nothing was forth coming. We started to get worried that we had been the victim of a serious banner snatch, until Buff popped into his tent to grab a sweatshirt and found the banner spread out on his sleeping bag with a big note - Gotcha! - Our female leaders (Becky and Michelle) had decided to play a trick on us all and had stolen our own banner! Beware next time ladies!!

item.title: Sheep rustling...
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: During the week, our flock of sheep had been placed secretly throughout the Jamboree site. Some had attached themselves to the main flag pole, others to the local "camel" and still others to camp gateways and mess tents. These new additions were loved by their new Scouting friends....until they went missing one evening! A ransom note duly arrived the next day telling us to be waiting by the showers at 5pm and to bring "ducks" and a Welsh Flag necker. 5pm saw our covert assault team armed with water pistols, carefully hidden nearby. Then our sheep were spotted being expertly marshaled by a "shepard" and his sheep dogs. A professional round up by the dogs, who were following signals from their masters whistle, then  ensued before chaos erupted when our assault team leapt out of hiding and fired water at everyone! A group photo with Red Bandits ESU ended a brilliant and very funny activity.

item.title: Team Lube...blck ops!
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Allegedly, members of FreeSpirit's blacks ops team (known as Team Lube) were out and about in search of some serious booty. Dodging roving security teams, a target was spotted, a plan of attack was formulated and expertly carried out with another "alleged" banner added to our collection....possibly the main banner from the BP!!!

item.title: A big thank you
item.dc:creator: buff
item.content:encoded: Thanking you all - members of FreeSpirit, parents and especially my fellow leaders - for a great camp. Lots of fun, new friends made, old friendships renewed. We certainly left our mark on the camp...onwards and upwards! See you all at Birthday Camp end of the month - Buff.
